<p>Documentation of <code>SerialPort</code> <code>Write</code> says that</p>  <blockquote>   <p>By default, SerialPort uses ASCIIEncoding to encode the characters.   ASCIIEncoding encodes all characters greater than 127 as (char)63 or   '?'. To support additional characters in that range, set Encoding to   UTF8Encoding, UTF32Encoding, or UnicodeEncoding.</p> </blockquote>  <p>Also see <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11466800/c-sharp-serialport-write-not-sending-all-bytes-when-0xcc-in-array">here</a>. Does this mean I can't send byte array using <code>write</code>?</p>